  "body": "**Background**: https://roughtime.googlesource.com/roughtime\r\n\r\n**Problem to solve**: NTP (network time protocol) responses are insecure and may be subject to MITM attacks. This is especially risky if the host machine only synchronizes its clock every few hours. \r\n\r\n**Summary**: Roughtime is a project that aims to provide secure time synchronisation. Roughtime can resolve clock time within <10s acceptance (typically <1s accuracy). This lowers the attack damage to less than 1 epoch and could be a helpful security feature for alerting node operators of potential NTP issues.\r\n\r\nThanks to @CarlBeek for bringing it up. ",
